WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.600 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.600 --> 00:00:17.410 align:middle line:84%
>> Being at our first peak,
Kedarnath, at the Shiva temple,

00:00:17.410 --> 00:00:21.130 align:middle line:84%
has awakened our potential
for strength but also some

00:00:21.130 --> 00:00:25.720 align:middle line:84%
of our petty comforts--
cravings, weakness, and ego.

00:00:25.720 --> 00:00:29.170 align:middle line:84%
For some people, these
shadows still lay dormant--

00:00:29.170 --> 00:00:31.970 align:middle line:90%
violence just waiting to happen.

00:00:31.970 --> 00:00:34.540 align:middle line:84%
But that's why we
come on pilgrimage--

00:00:34.540 --> 00:00:38.080 align:middle line:84%
to reveal our shadows
before their grip on us

00:00:38.080 --> 00:00:40.525 align:middle line:84%
steals the very freedom
we came here to find.

00:00:40.525 --> 00:00:43.140 align:middle line:90%


00:00:43.140 --> 00:00:46.640 align:middle line:84%
>> So there can be 10 people
present to one experience,

00:00:46.640 --> 00:00:49.580 align:middle line:84%
and they will all describe
it in their own way through

00:00:49.580 --> 00:00:54.290 align:middle line:84%
the looking glass, which has
been conditioned not only

00:00:54.290 --> 00:00:56.540 align:middle line:84%
by their history, but also
conditioned by their idea

00:00:56.540 --> 00:00:57.340 align:middle line:90%
of the future.

00:00:57.340 --> 00:01:00.790 align:middle line:90%


00:01:00.790 --> 00:01:03.040 align:middle line:84%
See, our present is
enslaved by your past

00:01:03.040 --> 00:01:07.390 align:middle line:84%
and also what you want in
the future, so life slips by.

00:01:07.390 --> 00:01:09.010 align:middle line:90%
You never live it.

00:01:09.010 --> 00:01:11.773 align:middle line:84%
Good life only happens
in the present.

00:01:11.773 --> 00:01:13.690 align:middle line:84%
And, mostly, we are
taught to use the present,

00:01:13.690 --> 00:01:16.148 align:middle line:84%
to manipulate the present--
either to escape from the past,

00:01:16.148 --> 00:01:19.480 align:middle line:84%
or somehow lead us to a
Utopian future, which only

00:01:19.480 --> 00:01:20.950 align:middle line:90%
exists as an idea in our heads.

00:01:20.950 --> 00:01:23.520 align:middle line:90%


00:01:23.520 --> 00:01:25.260 align:middle line:84%
Until there is no
inner violence within,

00:01:25.260 --> 00:01:28.350 align:middle line:84%
there's no end of violence
without because the law is--

00:01:28.350 --> 00:01:31.627 align:middle line:84%
as within so without,
not vise versa.

00:01:31.627 --> 00:01:34.609 align:middle line:90%


00:01:34.609 --> 00:01:38.088 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:01:38.088 --> 00:01:44.052 align:middle line:90%


00:01:44.052 --> 00:01:47.531 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:47.531 --> 00:02:24.840 align:middle line:90%


00:02:24.840 --> 00:02:27.340 align:middle line:84%
>> This is not a
journey to feel better.

00:02:27.340 --> 00:02:28.890 align:middle line:90%
Do you understand?

00:02:28.890 --> 00:02:30.180 align:middle line:90%
You come here to transcend.

00:02:30.180 --> 00:02:33.603 align:middle line:90%
[VOCALIZING]

00:02:33.603 --> 00:02:49.770 align:middle line:90%


00:02:49.770 --> 00:02:52.350 align:middle line:10%
>> We were all told to bring
sleeping bags for the trip.

00:02:52.350 --> 00:02:55.470 align:middle line:10%
So we get to Rishikesh,
and we're getting

00:02:55.470 --> 00:02:57.540 align:middle line:10%
ready to prepare for our trip.

00:02:57.540 --> 00:03:01.950 align:middle line:84%
Anand said, you don't really
need your sleeping bags.

00:03:01.950 --> 00:03:03.660 align:middle line:90%
It's not really necessary.

00:03:03.660 --> 00:03:06.870 align:middle line:10%
>> If you want to carry
it when you go hiking,

00:03:06.870 --> 00:03:09.540 align:middle line:10%
it'll be more comfortable
up in the village.

00:03:09.540 --> 00:03:13.110 align:middle line:84%
But they have supplied
bedding for us.

00:03:13.110 --> 00:03:16.020 align:middle line:90%
>> So we probably won't need it.

00:03:16.020 --> 00:03:19.950 align:middle line:84%
>> And they left their bags
behind at the Sattva center,

00:03:19.950 --> 00:03:21.810 align:middle line:90%
and it's cold--

00:03:21.810 --> 00:03:22.770 align:middle line:90%
freezing.

00:03:22.770 --> 00:03:24.810 align:middle line:84%
And people didn't have
their sleeping bags,

00:03:24.810 --> 00:03:27.120 align:middle line:84%
and everything
feels damp and wet.

00:03:27.120 --> 00:03:30.270 align:middle line:90%
People were beside themselves.

00:03:30.270 --> 00:03:34.380 align:middle line:84%
Not just beside themselves,
but like angry and pissed

00:03:34.380 --> 00:03:36.122 align:middle line:90%
and at Anand.

00:03:36.122 --> 00:03:39.496 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:03:39.496 --> 00:03:45.770 align:middle line:90%


00:03:45.770 --> 00:03:50.400 align:middle line:10%
>> The intuition said, take
it, but you said don't take it.

00:03:50.400 --> 00:03:52.194 align:middle line:10%
So I said, I'm trusting you.

00:03:52.194 --> 00:03:54.010 align:middle line:10%
I left it.

00:03:54.010 --> 00:03:55.090 align:middle line:90%
>> You trusted me, right?

00:03:55.090 --> 00:03:57.750 align:middle line:90%
