00:04:11.830 --> 00:04:14.550 align:middle line:90%
That's what I think.

00:04:14.550 --> 00:04:17.800 align:middle line:84%
Do you really need
what do you think?

00:04:17.800 --> 00:04:19.720 align:middle line:84%
Isn't that why the
conflict in our world

00:04:19.720 --> 00:04:22.670 align:middle line:84%
keeps happening
all over the world?

00:04:22.670 --> 00:04:25.300 align:middle line:84%
I've seen good people
turn violent at the turn

00:04:25.300 --> 00:04:27.830 align:middle line:90%
of circumstance.

00:04:27.830 --> 00:04:29.302 align:middle line:90%
Have you ever seen it?

00:04:29.302 --> 00:04:31.010 align:middle line:84%
People you thought
were like, oh, nothing

00:04:31.010 --> 00:04:32.510 align:middle line:90%
would happen-- poof.

00:04:32.510 --> 00:04:35.780 align:middle line:90%
Wow, where did that come from?

00:04:35.780 --> 00:04:38.450 align:middle line:84%
It can happen to any
person at any time.

00:04:38.450 --> 00:04:39.590 align:middle line:90%
It can be something else.

00:04:39.590 --> 00:04:41.215 align:middle line:84%
It's never the same
thing for everyone.

00:04:41.215 --> 00:04:43.010 align:middle line:84%
And somebody has a
trigger out of a bed,

00:04:43.010 --> 00:04:45.030 align:middle line:84%
or somebody has-- these
other triggers, you see?

00:04:45.030 --> 00:04:47.450 align:middle line:84%
We are all in magnificence
when the circumstances

00:04:47.450 --> 00:04:52.400 align:middle line:84%
are within our
familiar state, right?

00:04:52.400 --> 00:04:55.040 align:middle line:84%
But the moment you are faced
with the unfamiliar, what

00:04:55.040 --> 00:04:58.340 align:middle line:90%
comes up is terror.

00:04:58.340 --> 00:05:00.050 align:middle line:84%
And what comes for
some, is terror.

00:05:00.050 --> 00:05:02.970 align:middle line:90%
Within that terror, is blame.

00:05:02.970 --> 00:05:04.560 align:middle line:84%
Some people would
blame yourself.

00:05:04.560 --> 00:05:06.977 align:middle line:84%
Then you would project that
blame on somebody else.

00:05:06.977 --> 00:05:09.060 align:middle line:84%
It might be me if you
didn't bring a sleeping bag,

00:05:09.060 --> 00:05:11.146 align:middle line:84%
so somebody might be
blaming me right now.

00:05:11.146 --> 00:05:13.530 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:05:13.530 --> 00:05:15.450 align:middle line:90%
Any person at any time--

00:05:15.450 --> 00:05:16.620 align:middle line:90%
it can be something else.

00:05:16.620 --> 00:05:19.660 align:middle line:84%
Somebody can be triggered
by something else.

00:05:19.660 --> 00:05:23.310 align:middle line:84%
It's never the same
thing for everyone.

00:05:23.310 --> 00:05:24.215 align:middle line:90%
It can happen to me.

00:05:24.215 --> 00:05:25.090 align:middle line:90%
It can happen to you.

00:05:25.090 --> 00:05:27.048 align:middle line:84%
It can happen to anyone
in a different position

00:05:27.048 --> 00:05:29.520 align:middle line:84%
at a different
circumstance in life

00:05:29.520 --> 00:05:33.490 align:middle line:84%
where we give up our power, we
play the victim, and we blame.

00:05:33.490 --> 00:05:36.570 align:middle line:90%


00:05:36.570 --> 00:05:39.070 align:middle line:84%
That's why we are even bringing
attention to it because it's

00:05:39.070 --> 00:05:41.110 align:middle line:84%
very easy to not
bring attention to it

00:05:41.110 --> 00:05:43.750 align:middle line:84%
because today is another day,
and it's beautiful, isn't it?

00:05:43.750 --> 00:05:45.880 align:middle line:90%
You are all feeling differently.

00:05:45.880 --> 00:05:47.950 align:middle line:84%
And we can just stay
here four more hours,

00:05:47.950 --> 00:05:49.466 align:middle line:84%
and then you will
feel differently.

00:05:49.466 --> 00:05:53.200 align:middle line:90%


00:05:53.200 --> 00:05:54.760 align:middle line:90%
But that's life.

00:05:54.760 --> 00:05:56.350 align:middle line:90%
Life is such.

00:05:56.350 --> 00:05:59.200 align:middle line:90%
Life never promises monotony.

00:05:59.200 --> 00:06:02.365 align:middle line:84%
Life never promises
you the known.

00:06:02.365 --> 00:06:05.960 align:middle line:84%
Life is a journey into the
unknown-- the great mystery.

00:06:05.960 --> 00:06:08.180 align:middle line:84%
And our life is marked
by events which we never

00:06:08.180 --> 00:06:09.090 align:middle line:90%
thought would happen.

00:06:09.090 --> 00:06:14.460 align:middle line:84%
Those are what define us, change
us, alter our existence, see?

00:06:14.460 --> 00:06:16.470 align:middle line:84%
Until we are not in
love with the unknown,

00:06:16.470 --> 00:06:19.090 align:middle line:90%
we are constantly threatened--

00:06:19.090 --> 00:06:24.419 align:middle line:84%
the unfamiliar, the
uncomfortable, the terrifying.

00:06:24.419 --> 00:06:29.800 align:middle line:90%


00:06:29.800 --> 00:06:31.420 align:middle line:84%
So you have to be
in the unfamiliar.

00:06:31.420 --> 00:06:33.060 align:middle line:90%
There has to be discontinue.

00:06:33.060 --> 00:06:35.450 align:middle line:90%
That's why we are here.

00:06:35.450 --> 00:06:38.277 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing wrong with
Sydney or LA or any of that,

00:06:38.277 --> 00:06:39.110 align:middle line:90%
but it's continuous.

00:06:39.110 --> 00:06:40.640 align:middle line:84%
You see, you have to
much stories and too much

00:06:40.640 --> 00:06:42.230 align:middle line:84%
familiarity there--
too much hooks

00:06:42.230 --> 00:06:45.960 align:middle line:84%
to define yourself with, to find
your safety escape mechanism.

00:06:45.960 --> 00:06:52.970 align:middle line:10%
Here, there is no place
to escape, nowhere to go.

00:06:52.970 --> 00:06:53.770 align:middle line:90%
Is it not?

00:06:53.770 --> 00:06:56.560 align:middle line:84%
Do you realize, the moment
we have an escape position,

00:06:56.560 --> 00:06:57.760 align:middle line:90%
you take it.

00:06:57.760 --> 00:07:00.095 align:middle line:90%
Is it not?

00:07:00.095 --> 00:07:02.720 align:middle line:84%
Most people, the moment that is
a-- you are in a trigger stage,

00:07:02.720 --> 00:07:04.428 align:middle line:84%
and there is an escape
route, we take it.

00:07:04.428 --> 00:07:06.210 align:middle line:90%
Most people will take that.

00:07:06.210 --> 00:07:08.710 align:middle line:84%
That's why everybody wants to
experience the [NON-ENGLISH],,

00:07:08.710 --> 00:07:09.910 align:middle line:90%
but very, very few do.

00:07:09.910 --> 00:07:13.220 align:middle line:90%


00:07:13.220 --> 00:07:15.650 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to go
out and be Mother Teresa

00:07:15.650 --> 00:07:17.840 align:middle line:84%
and convert everybody
to Christianity.

00:07:17.840 --> 00:07:23.170 align:middle line:84%
But we have to live
authentically--

00:07:23.170 --> 00:07:26.650 align:middle line:84%
every moment, and simple
moments as a little hike,

00:07:26.650 --> 00:07:30.230 align:middle line:84%
and simple moments
when you feel cold.

00:07:30.230 --> 00:07:33.110 align:middle line:84%
You have to realize that there
are people sleeping naked

00:07:33.110 --> 00:07:37.520 align:middle line:84%
